# Build-time tarball sent to the Docker daemon. Everything here is omitted
# from the image build context (and therefore from any `COPY .` in the
# Dockerfile). Keep this list narrow — files the running app reads at
# runtime MUST stay in the context.

# Source control + CI metadata
.git
.github

# Build outputs and dependency caches (rebuilt inside the image)
.next
node_modules

# Runtime / operator data (must never bake into the image)
backups
uploads

# Secrets
.env
.env.*

# Log junk
npm-debug.log*

# Dockerfile + compose are read by the daemon/orchestrator, not by the image
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml

# Docs
# README.md and docs/ are not read by the app at runtime — safe to omit.
# CHANGELOG.md IS read at runtime by src/app/changelog/page.tsx
#   (fs.readFileSync(process.cwd()+'/CHANGELOG.md')) so it MUST stay in
#   the image. Likewise USER_MANUAL_TH.md is read by src/app/manual/page.tsx
#   — also stays.
README.md
docs
